    *****************************************************************
    * WARNING: The 'project' command is now deprecated, this legacy *
    * link to the new executable, turnincfg, may disappear in any   *
    * future release.                                               *
    *****************************************************************
Usage: project [options] [project name]

Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -d, --disable         Disable submissions for the current project.
  -D, --perm-disable    Permanently disable submissions for the current
                        project.
  -e, --enable          Enable submissions for the current project and make it
                        the default project.
  -l                    Enable submissions for the current project but don't
                        make it default.
  -r, --remove          Remove the current project and all associated files.
  -i, --init            Initialize this project.
  -p, --compress        Compress this project.
  -x, --extract         Extract this project.
  -v, --verify          Verify signatures on submitted projects.
  --list                Lists projects for the course. Also displays wether or
                        not the project is enabled.
  -c COURSE, --course=COURSE
                        Course name
  -C CONFIG, --config=CONFIG
                        Use an alternate config file.
  -w, --legal           Print warranty and license information.

  Administrative options:
    These options can add or remove courses, etc.

    --create-course=CREATE_COURSE
                        Creates a course.
    --delete-course=DELETE_COURSE
                        Deletes a course.
    --archive-course=ARCHIVE_COURSE
                        Archive a course.
